sentences.english: I pulled the throttles to idle just south of Sicily , but we still overran the refueling tanker awaiting us over Gibraltar.
sentences.chinese: 即便如此我們還是超過了直布羅陀的加油機。

sentences.english: The Song Mountain was named as the "Oriental Gibraltar" by American military experts.
sentences.chinese: 松山被美國軍事家稱爲“東方直布羅陀”。

sentences.english: However, it is still subject to laws in the UK.
sentences.chinese: 然而，直布羅陀仍然受到英國法律的約束。

sentences.english: The ship called at Gibraltar to coal.
sentences.chinese: 這艘輪船停靠於直布羅陀港加煤。

sentences.english: The great Rock of Gibralter finally loomed out of its concealing haze.
sentences.chinese: 偉大之直布羅陀堡壘最後從隱蔽的霞霧中出現。

sentences.english: Your objective is to penetrate the radar installations of Gibralter.
sentences.chinese: 你們的任務是穿越直布羅陀的雷達防線。

sentences.english: However, it seems the real power lies in the hands of the Barbary Apes.
sentences.chinese: 然而，直布羅陀的實權似乎操控在叟猴手上。

sentences.english: I tentatively decided, unless conditions should improve, to divert the expedition into Gibraltar.
sentences.chinese: 我臨時決定，除非情況轉佳，將遠征軍開向直布羅陀。

sentences.english: One sailor jumped ship at Gibraltar.
sentences.chinese: 一水手在直布羅陀棄職離船。

sentences.english: Sikorski died in a plane crash in Gibraltar a year later.
sentences.chinese: 一年以後，希科爾斯基在直布羅陀的一場空難中遇害。
許多船在直布羅陀加煤。

sentences.english: The Rock of Gibraltar is honeycombed with caves.
sentences.chinese: 直布羅陀巖山上有許多洞穴。
